e does show that Iran initiated a major closure meeting the market rule's definition. The plaintiff has identified multiple consistent secondary reports that converge on the same core facts, and even the defense's evidence (DX-1) partially corroborates the closure's existence while disputing the \"new\" nature of the notice.\n\nThe evidence shows:\n- Iran's civil aviation authority issued instructions for western Tehran FIR closure\n- It was effective before the deadline (May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET)\n- It was not weather-related (security context)\n- Western Tehran FIR qualifies as a major Iranian airspace region under the market rule\n- The rule specifically states that limited exceptions don't disqualify such a closure\n\nTherefore, the proposition should be \"demonstrated.\"\n\nBut let's be precise about what \"demonstrated\" means - it means the evidence shows the proposition is more likely true than not. There are reasonable doubts, but based on the consistent evidence from multiple sources and even the defense's own admission of some closure, I believe the preponderance standard is met.\n\nI should make sure I use the exact tool call format: `mcp` with tool `aar_submit_council_vote` and arguments as JSON string.\n\nThe rationale needs to be very brief - no more than 3 sentences.\n\nLet me draft a rationale:\n\"The admitted evidence from multiple credible sources consistently shows Iran's civil aviation authority imposed a western Tehran FIR closure with limited exceptions, effective before the deadline, for security reasons. The record confirms this qualifies as a major closure of a major Iranian airspace region under the rule, which permits limited exceptions. The preponderance of evidence supports the proposition.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a0f146d433d54ca58e91a1","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"{\"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking"